<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">Three real paths, same destination: a complete Habitability Framework for Earth, Mars, and your chosen exoplanet.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have completed the Habitability Framework Template for Earth, Mars, and my chosen exoplanet — and I can defend at least one classification under questioning.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Solo build-first</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Work through the 5-field template alone. Fill in 5–7 criteria for Earth as the baseline, then evaluate Mars and your exoplanet against each. Use the worked example in Concepts as your model. Color-code each cell MEETS / PARTIAL / FAILS as you go.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Independent · Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Criterion deep-dive (pair)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">With a partner, pick one criterion category — temperature / water / atmosphere / magnetic field / planetary mass / host star / orbital geometry. Build that criterion really well across all 5 fields for Earth, Mars, and both your exoplanets. Then teach it to two other pairs. Each pair leaves with three completed criteria from their own work plus two from the jigsaw.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Verbal · Pair · Jigsaw</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI-coached</div>
